@node Overview
@chapter Overview

The Heirloom Darwin port ships five packages:

@table @asis
@item @b{sh}
Ritter's SVR4-personality Bourne shell.  Backticks, no
@code{$(@dots{})}.  Historical semantics preserved.

@item @b{devtools}
@command{make} (SVR4 flavour), @command{sccs}, @command{yacc},
@command{lex}, @command{m4}.

@item @b{toolchest}
200+ POSIX/SVR4 utilities.  Each tool compiled into up to five
personality variants (default SVID3, POSIX/SUS, POSIX-2001/SUS3,
S42/SVID4-subset, UCB/BSD).

@item @b{doctools}
The Bell Labs troff preprocessor pipeline: @command{soelim} →
@command{refer} → @command{grap} → @command{pic} → @command{tbl} →
@command{eqn} → @command{troff}.

@item @b{pkgtools}
SVR4 package administration: @command{pkgadd}, @command{pkgrm},
@command{pkgchk}, @command{pkginfo}, @command{pkgmk}, @command{pkgproto},
@command{pkgtrans}.
@end table

Plus a shared workspace repo holding hardening artefacts, ALM
scaffolding, and QA reports.

@node Modality
@chapter Modality

Every installed binary honours three axes of behaviour:

@table @asis
@item VERSION
The port revision.  Reported by @option{--version}.  Pinnable via
@env{HEIRLOOM_PORT_VERSION_REQ}.

@item VARIANT
Which SVR4 personality binary is invoked.  Directory-based:
@file{$PREFIX/bin/@var{tool}} (SVID3 default),
@file{$PREFIX/bin/posix/@var{tool}} (SUS),
@file{$PREFIX/bin/posix2001/@var{tool}} (SUS3),
@file{$PREFIX/bin/s42/@var{tool}} (SVID4),
@file{$PREFIX/ucb/@var{tool}} (UCB/BSD),
@file{$PREFIX/ccs/bin/@var{tool}} (CCS).

@item DIALECT
Human-friendly synonym for VARIANT.  Recognised: @code{svid3},
@code{svr3}, @code{svr4}, @code{sysv}, @code{sysv3}, @code{posix},
@code{sus}, @code{sus2}, @code{posix2001}, @code{sus3}, @code{s42},
@code{svid4}, @code{ucb}, @code{bsd}, @code{ccs}.
@end table

Selection precedence (highest wins):

@enumerate
@item Command-line: @option{--variant=@var{name}} or
      @option{--dialect=@var{name}}
@item @env{HEIRLOOM_VARIANT}
@item @env{HEIRLOOM_DIALECT}
@item @env{SYSV3} (Ritter's classic SVID3 selector)
@item Compile-time default
@end enumerate

Full detail: @command{man 7 heirloom-modality}.

